## Plan Summary

**One file to change:** `src/routes.ts`

Here's what I found and what needs to happen:

### Current state
The handler is a one-liner that dumps the raw array: `res.json(users)`. The tests in `tests/routes.test.ts` **already expect the paginated shape** (with `data` + `pagination`), so they're currently failing.

### The fix (full handler replacement)
```typescript
router.get("/users", (req, res) => {
  const page  = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.page  as string) || 1);
  const limit = Math.max(1, parseInt(req.query.limit as string) || 10);

  const total      = users.length;
  const totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);
  const start      = (page - 1) * limit;
  const data       = users.slice(start, start + limit); // naturally [] when out of range

  res.json({
    data,
    pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages },
  });
});
```

### Why this covers all requirements
| Requirement | How it's handled |
|---|---|
| `page` defaults to 1, `limit` defaults to 10 | `parseInt(...) \|\| default` |
| Invalid/missing params don't crash | `Math.max(1, ...)` + fallback |
| Out-of-range page → empty `data`, not an error | `Array.slice` returns `[]` naturally when `start >= total`; still 200 |
| Correct response shape | `{ data, pagination: { page, limit, total, totalPages } }` |
| All 6 tests pass (4 new + 2 existing `/users/:id`) | No other files touched |

No other files need to be modified — `src/data.ts`, `src/types.ts`, and `src/app.ts` are all unchanged.
